This paper is primarily focused on the application of generative adversarial networks (GANs) to the problem of computing optimal transport maps, which is a problem in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed method to image data, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of the $2$-Wasserstein metric, which is a concept from numerical analysis and optimization, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for computing optimal transport maps, which could be considered a contribution to the field of signal processing, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.SI (Signal Processing).
